The paper discusses the use of tracking technologies in retail spaces, which involves a combination of computer science and human-computer interaction (HCI) concepts. Therefore, cs.CY (Computer Systems and Networking) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are likely categories. The paper also discusses privacy concerns and legal frameworks, which fall under cs.PR (Privacy and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of emotion detection systems and personalization, which are related to HCI and user experience, and thus cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a likely category.
